data.enText: the main, bottom part of a ship, that goes in the water

data.chText: 他们爬上了倾覆的船体，等候救援。
data.enText: They climbed onto the upturned hull and waited to be rescued.

data.chText: 剥去（豌豆、大豆等的）外壳；摘掉（草莓的）花萼
data.enText: to remove the outer covering of peas , beans , etc. or the ring of leaves attached to strawberries

means: 剥去(豌豆、大豆等的)外壳

tr: the frame or body of ship
persistent enlarged calyx at base of e.g. a strawberry or raspberry
dry outer covering of a fruit or seed or nut

value.def: The hull of a boat or tank is the main body of it.

example.ex: The hull had suffered extensive damage to the starboard side.

value.def: The hull of a soft fruit such as a strawberry is the stalk and ring of leaves at the base.
If you hull soft fruit such as strawberries, you remove the hulls.

example.tran: 洗一下草莓，并摘掉花萼。

value.tran: 除去（草莓等浆果）的花萼
